DEPHECTO TASK LIST (-*- text -*-)
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
$Id: $

- Define database schema
  - users
    - login
    - email
    - full name
    - disabled :boolean
    - admin :boolean
  - projects
    - has_many :components
    - defaultmilestone
    - name
    - description
    - archived (no new entries)
    - votesperuser
    - votestoconfirm
  - components
    - belongs_to :project
    - has_many :issues
    - description
    - default assignee
    - name
  - issues
    - belongs_to :component
    - has_many :comments
    - has_many :votes
    - has_many :tags
    - has_one :status
    - has_one :severity
    - has_one :resolution
    - has_one :type
    - has_one :milestone
    - has_one :version
    - assignee
    - reporter
    - summary
    - description => stored as a comment
    - due_date
  - resolutions
    - sortkey
    - value
      (fixed, invalid, wontfix, duplicate, worksforme, later)
    - archived
  - status
    - sortkey
    - value
      (unconfirmed, new, assigned, reopened, resolved, verified, closed)
    - archived
  - severities
    - sortkey
    - value
      (blocker, critical, major, minor, trivial)
    - archived
  - types
    - sortkey
    - value
      (defect, improvement, feature)
    - archived
  - comments
    - belongs_to :issue
    - datestamp
    - user
    - comment
    - type (for generated comments)
  - votes
    - belongs_to :issue
    - user
    - count (how many votes user applied to issue)
  - milestones
    - belongs_to :project
    - value
    - sort key for ordering in UI
    - assigned dates for ordering in search results
  - versions
    - belongs_to :project
    - value
  - attachments
    (store attachment data in separate table)
    - belongs_to :issue
    - user
    - datestamp
    - content type
    - filename
    - description
    - archived
  - tags
    - belongs_to :issue
    - value
  - dependencies
    - blocked by
    - depends on
  - duplicates
    - dupe #
    - dupe of
  - history
    - field changed
    - added value of the new field value (as string)
    - removed value if field value was deleted (as string)
    - attachment ID, if a file was attached
    - datestamp
    - user
  - cc or star
    - users who want notification when issues change
    - belongs_to :issue
    - user
